<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="256" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1185]" pageId="19" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1123,1149]" pageId="19" pageNumber="256">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[830,922,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="256">serratus</emphasis>
, referring to the dorsal process of the sacculus serrulate on the outer margin.
</paragraph>
